	The Company does not adopt a new arrangement that would be aggregated with any terminated arrangement under Section 409A at any time within the three-year period following the date of termination of the Plan; and
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-LEFT: 36PT; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(E)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	The termination does not occur proximate to a downturn in the financial health of the Company.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(ii)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	The Company, at its discretion, may terminate the Plan within 12 months of a corporate dissolution taxed under Section 331 of the Code, or with the approval of a bankruptcy court pursuant to 11 U.S.C. &#167;503(b)(1)(A), provided that amounts deferred under the Plan are included in the gross income of Participants in the latest of the following years (or, if earlier, the taxable year in which the amount is actually or constructively received):
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-LEFT: 36PT; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(A)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	The calendar year in which the Plan termination occurs;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAKAREA" STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 10PT; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN-TOP: 10PT">
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGENUMBERAREA" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	14
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAK" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS">
<HR STYLE="BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 0PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 0PX; WIDTH: 100%; BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 0PX; COLOR: #000000; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN: 4PX 0PX; BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 0PX; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="NOSHADE">
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage108"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-LEFT: 36PT; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(B)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	The first calendar year in which the amount is no longer subject to a substantial risk of forfeiture; or
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-LEFT: 36PT; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(C)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	The first calendar year in which the payment is administratively practicable;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(iii)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	The Company, at its discretion, may terminate the Plan pursuant to irrevocable action taken by the Company within the 30 days preceding or the 12 months following a Change in Control, provided:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-LEFT: 36PT; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(A)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	All agreements, methods, programs and other arrangements sponsored by the Company (or its successor) immediately after the Change in Control which are treated as a single plan under Section 1.409A-1(c)(2) of the Regulation are also terminated;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-LEFT: 36PT; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(B)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	All payments to Participants due under the Plan are made within 12 months of the date of the Plan's termination; and
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-LEFT: 36PT; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(C)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	All participants under the other terminated similar arrangements described in clause (i) are required to receive all amounts of deferred compensation within 12 months of the action taken by the Company (or its successor) to terminate such arrangements.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(iv)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	In accordance with such other events and conditions as may be prescribed by the Secretary of the Treasury in generally applicable guidance published in the Internal Revenue Bulletin.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	If the Plan is terminated pursuant to this Section 12.1(b) at a date other than the date that the Company additions would normally be credited to Participant's accounts, the Company may make, in the Compensation Committee's sole discretion, a pro-rated discretionary Company addition to each Participant's Account based on operating earnings of the Company generated through the date the Plan is terminated.
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	12.2
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	No Liability for Plan Amendment or Termination
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; Neither the Company, nor any officer, nor any Compensation Committee member thereof shall have any liability as a result of the amendment or termination of the Plan (including a termination pursuant to Section 13.1 below).&#160; Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Company shall have no liability for terminating the Plan notwithstanding the fact that a Participant may have expected to have future allocations made on Participant's behalf hereunder had the Plan remained in effect.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT">
	Section 13.&#160; Change in Control
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	13.1
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Change in Control
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; Notwithstanding any other provision of the Plan to the contrary, if the Company is involved in a Change in Control, the Plan will be terminated in accordance with Section 12.1(b) and Section 409A and all amounts deferred, including any growth additions and Company additions, will immediately vest and be paid out to the Participants in accordance with Section 12.1(b) and Section 409A.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT">
	Section 14.&#160; Requirements of Law
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	14.1
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Requirements of Law
</U>
</FONT>
	. The payment of cash pursuant to this Plan shall be subject to all applicable laws, rules and regulations as may be required.
</FONT>
</DIV>

</DIV>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	14.2
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Governing Law
</U>
</FONT>
	. The Plan, and all agreements hereunder, shall be construed in accordance with and governed by the laws of the State of Tennessee.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT">
	Section 15.&#160; Withholding Taxes
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	15.1
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Withholding Taxes
</U>
</FONT>
	. The Company shall have the right to deduct from all payments under this Plan an amount necessary to satisfy any Federal, state, or local withholding tax requirements.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 12PT">

<U>
	Effective Date
</U>
</FONT>
	. This Amended and Restated Plan shall become effective as of December 3, 2015 (the "Effective Date").

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Agreement
</U>
</FONT>
	"), dated
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">

	(the "

</U>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Company
</U>
</FONT>
	"), and
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">

	Employment Agreement
</U>
</FONT>
	"), or in the absence of an Employment Agreement or if not defined in the Employment Agreement, then the meanings given to them in the Plan.

</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	Section 1.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Market Stock Unit Award; Performance Goals
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; Subject to adjustment as set forth herein, the Grantee is hereby granted
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	NUMBER OF UNITS
</FONT>
	restricted stock units (the "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Target Award
</U>
</FONT>
	") under the Plan, with the specific
</FONT>
	number of restricted stock units earned to be determined in accordance with
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
</FONT>
	hereto (the "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Market Stock Units
</U>
</FONT>
	").&#160; Each Market Stock Unit represents the right to receive one share of the Company's Common Stock, $.001 par value (the "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Stock
</U>
</FONT>
	"), subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement and the Plan.&#160; Except as otherwise provided in
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 3
</U>
</FONT>
	or
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 5.2
</U>
</FONT>
	, before the Market Stock Units will be earned and settled, the Committee must certify the level of achievement of the Performance Goals described in
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
</FONT>
	hereto which the Committee shall do as soon as practicable after the third anniversary of the Grant Date (the "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	End Date of the Performance Period
</U>
</FONT>
	", and such period, the "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Performance Period
</U>
</FONT>
	").&#160; Any Market Stock Units that are not earned as a result of the level of achievement of the Performance Goals at the End Date of the Performance Period shall be immediately forfeited as of the End Date of the Performance Period.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	Section 2.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Vesting of the Award
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; Except as otherwise provided in
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 3
</U>
</FONT>
	and
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 5.2
</U>
</FONT>
	below, 100% of the Market Stock Units determined by the Committee to be earned pursuant to
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 1
</U>
</FONT>
	hereof will vest on the End Date of the Performance Period (the "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Vesting Date
</U>
</FONT>
	"), as long as the Grantee is serving as an employee of the Company on such date.&#160; The Company shall issue one share of the Stock to the Grantee in settlement of each earned and vested Market Stock Unit (in the aggregate, the "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Distributed Shares
</U>
</FONT>
	") at the time the Market Stock Unit vests pursuant to this Agreement.&#160; The Distributed Shares shall be represented by a certificate or by a book-entry.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	Section 3.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Forfeiture on Termination of Employment
</U>
</FONT>
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	3.1.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Termination by the Company for Cause
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; If the Grantee's employment with the Company is involuntarily terminated for Cause prior to the End Date of the Performance Period, then all Market Stock Units will be forfeited and the Grantee shall have no further rights with respect to such Market Stock Units.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAKAREA" STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 10PT; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN-TOP: 10PT">
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGENUMBERAREA" STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAK" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS; COLOR: #000000">
<HR STYLE="BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 0PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 0PX; WIDTH: 100%; BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 0PX; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN: 4PX 0PX; BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 0PX; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="NOSHADE">
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage111"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	3.2.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Termination by the Company without Cause or by the Grantee for Good Reason
</U>
</FONT>
	. If Grantee's employment with the Company (a) is involuntarily terminated by the Company for any reason other than termination for Cause, or (b) is terminated by the Grantee for Good Reason, then, subject to Grantee's execution of any release of claims provided for in the Employment Agreement, if applicable, the Vesting Date shall be the effective date of Grantee's termination of employment, and the number of Market Stock Units that shall vest (the "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Pro Rata Amount
</U>
</FONT>
	") shall be the product of (i) a fraction, the numerator of which is the number of whole months during the Performance Period that the Grantee was employed by the Company, and the denominator of which is the number of months in the originally stated Performance Period, multiplied by (ii) the number of Market Stock Units that would vest pursuant to
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
</FONT>
	if the Performance Goals that had been achieved as of the Vesting Date were in fact achieved on the End Date of the Performance Period, as further described on
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
</FONT>
	. The Pro Rata Amount of Market Stock Units shall be settled in Stock issued to the Grantee as soon as practicable following the Vesting Date. For purposes of this
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 3.2
</U>
</FONT>
	, the terms "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Cause
</U>
</FONT>
	" and "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Good Reason
</U>
</FONT>
	" shall have the meanings set forth in the Employment Agreement, or in the absence of an Employment Agreement, the term "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Cause
</U>
</FONT>
	" shall have the meaning given to it in the Plan, and the term "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Good Reason
</U>
</FONT>
	" shall mean (i) a material reduction in the Grantee's base salary (unless such reduction is part of an across the board reduction affecting all Company executives with a comparable title), or (ii) a requirement by the Company to relocate the Grantee to a location that is greater than 25 miles from the location of the office in which the Grantee performs his or her duties at the time of such relocation.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	3.3.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Termination by Death or Disability
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; If the Grantee's employment with the Company terminates by reason of death or Disability (as defined in the Plan), then the Vesting Date shall be the date of Grantee's death or the effective date of Grantee's termination of employment on account of Disability, and the number of Market Stock Units that shall vest shall be the product of (i) a fraction, the numerator of which is the number of whole months during the Performance Period that the Grantee was employed by the Company, and the denominator of which is the number of months in the originally stated Performance Period, multiplied by (ii) the Target Award. The Market Stock Units shall be settled in Stock issued to the Grantee (or Grantee's estate or personal representative, as applicable) as soon as practicable following the Vesting Date.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF; TEXT-INDENT: 67.5PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	3.4&#160; &#160; &#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Termination by Reason of Retirement
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; If the Grantee's employment with the Company terminates by reason of Retirement (as defined in the Plan), the Market Stock Units granted hereunder shall not be forfeited but shall be settled in Stock to the Grantee in the manner as described in
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 2
</U>
</FONT>
	(or otherwise) as if the Grantee had continued employment through the Vesting Date (or such other vesting event pursuant to
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 3.3
</U>
</FONT>
	or
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 5.2
</U>
</FONT>
	) and based on actual performance of the Company as determined in accordance with&#160;Section 1&#160;and&#160;Exhibit A&#160;hereto.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	3.5.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Other Termination
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; Subject to
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 5.2
</U>
</FONT>
	, if the Grantee's employment with the Company terminates for any reason other than as described in
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Sections 3.1
</U>
</FONT>
	through
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	3.4
</U>
</FONT>
	above (or if Grantee fails to execute any release of claims pursuant to the Employment Agreement, if applicable), then all Market Stock Units that have not vested prior to the date of termination of Grantee's employment will be forfeited and the Grantee shall have no further rights with respect to such Market Stock Units.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</FONT>
</FONT>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAKAREA" STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 10PT; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN-TOP: 10PT">
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGENUMBERAREA" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	2
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAK" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS; COLOR: #000000">
<HR STYLE="BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 0PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 0PX; WIDTH: 100%; BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 0PX; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN: 4PX 0PX; BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 0PX; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="NOSHADE">
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage112"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	Section 4.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Voting Rights and Dividends
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; Prior to the Vesting Date, the Grantee shall be credited with cash dividend equivalents with respect to the Market Stock Units
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	&#160;
</FONT>
	at the time of any payment of dividends to stockholders on shares of Common Stock in accordance with the terms set forth in the Plan, and such dividend equivalents shall be paid (in cash, without interest) to the Grantee when the Market Stock Units to which they relate are settled in accordance with this Agreement.&#160; The Grantee shall not have any voting rights with respect to the Stock underlying the Market Stock Units prior to the vesting of the Market Stock Units and the issuance of the Stock as set forth in
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 2
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; A holder of Distributed Shares shall have full dividend and voting rights as a holder of Stock.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	Section 5.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Restrictions on Transfer; Change in Control
</U>
</FONT>
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	5.1.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	General Restrictions
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; The Market Stock Units shall not be transferable by the Grantee (or his or her personal representative or estate) other than by will or by the laws of descent and distribution.&#160; The terms of this Agreement shall be binding on the executors, administrators, heirs and successors of the Grantee.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	5.2.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Change in Control
</U>
</FONT>
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 108PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	If in connection with a Change in Control, the acquiring corporation (or other successor to the Company in the Change in Control) does not assume the Market Stock Units, then a number of Market Stock Units shall vest and be settled in Stock issued to the Grantee immediately prior to the Change in Control equal to the greater of (A) the Target Award, or (B) the number of Market Stock Units that would vest pursuant to
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
</FONT>
	if the Performance Goals that had been achieved as of the date of the Change in Control had in fact been achieved as of the End Date of the Performance Period.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 108PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	If in connection with a Change in Control, the acquiring corporation&#160; (or other successor to the Company in the Change in Control) assumes the Market Stock Units, and if Grantee's employment with the Company (or its successor company) (i) is involuntarily terminated within 12 months following a Change in Control for any reason other than termination for Cause, or (ii) is terminated by the Grantee for Good Reason within 12 months following a Change in Control, then subject to Grantee's execution of any release of claims set forth in the Employment Agreement, if applicable, the Vesting Date shall be the date of the termination of employment described in this
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 5.2(b)
</U>
</FONT>
	, and a number of Market Stock Units shall vest and be settled in Stock issued to the Grantee on the Vesting Date equal to the greater of (A) the Target Award, or (B) the number of Market Stock Units that would vest pursuant to
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
</FONT>
	if the Performance Goals that had been achieved as of the Vesting Date were in fact achieved as of the End Date of the Performance Period. For purposes of this
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 5.2(b
</U>
</FONT>
	), the terms "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Cause
</U>
</FONT>
	" and "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Good Reason
</U>
</FONT>
	" shall have the meanings set forth in
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 3.2
</U>
</FONT>
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	Section 6.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Restrictive Agreement
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; As a condition to the receipt of any Distributed Shares, the Grantee (or his or her legal representative or estate or any third party transferee), if the Company so requests, will execute an agreement in form satisfactory to the Company in which the Grantee or such other recipient of the shares represents that he or she is purchasing the shares for investment purposes, and not with a view to resale or distribution.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAKAREA" STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 10PT; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN-TOP: 10PT">
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGENUMBERAREA" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	3
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAK" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS; COLOR: #000000">
<HR STYLE="BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 0PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 0PX; WIDTH: 100%; BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 0PX; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN: 4PX 0PX; BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 0PX; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="NOSHADE">
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage113"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	Section 7.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Market Stock Units Award Subject to Recoupment Policy
</U>
</FONT>
	. The award of Market Stock Units is subject to the Healthways, Inc. Compensation Recoupment Policy (the "
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Policy
</U>
</FONT>
	").&#160; The award of Market Stock Units, or any amount traceable to the award of Market Stock Units, shall be subject to the recoupment obligations described in the Policy.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	Section 8.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Adjustment
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; In the event of any merger, reorganization, consolidation, recapitalization, extraordinary cash dividend, stock dividend, stock split or other change in corporate structure affecting the Stock, the number of Market Stock Units subject to this Agreement, as well as the performance criteria set forth on
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
</FONT>
	, shall be equitably and proportionately adjusted by the Committee in accordance with the Plan and the intent of this Agreement without duplication of
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 4
</U>
</FONT>
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	Section 9.
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Tax Withholding
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; The Company shall have the right to require the Grantee to remit to the Company an amount necessary to satisfy any federal, state and local withholding tax requirements attributable to the vesting and payment of the Market Stock Units prior to the delivery of the Distributed Shares, or may withhold from the Distributed Shares an amount of Stock having a Fair Market Value equal to such federal, state or local taxes as shall be required to be withheld pursuant to any applicable law or regulation.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">

<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Plan
</U>
</FONT>
	.&#160; This Agreement is made under and subject to the provisions of the Plan, and all of the provisions of the Plan that do not conflict with this Agreement are also provisions of this Agreement.&#160; If there is a difference or conflict between the provisions of this Agreement and the provisions of the Plan, the provisions of this Agreement will govern.&#160; By signing this Agreement, the Grantee confirms that he or she has received a copy of the Plan.
</FONT>

</DIV>

<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">

</U>
</FONT>
	In the event Grantee breaches any of the confidentiality, non-solicitation or non-compete covenants set forth in the Employment Agreement, if applicable, the Market Stock Units shall immediately thereupon expire and be forfeited, and the Company shall be entitled to seek other appropriate remedies it may have available in connection with such breach.

</FONT>
	.&#160; If, for any reason, any provision hereof shall be determined to be invalid or unenforceable, the validity and effect of the other provisions hereof shall not be affected thereby.&#160; Whenever possible, each provision of this Agreement will be interpreted in such manner as to be effective and valid under applicable law, but if any provision of this Agreement is held to be invalid, illegal or unenforceable in any respect under any applicable law or rule in any jurisdiction, such invalidity, illegality or unenforceability will not affect any other provision or any other jurisdiction, but this Agreement will be reformed, construed and enforced in such jurisdiction as if such invalid, illegal or unenforceable provision had never been contained herein.&#160; If any court determines that any provision of this Agreement is unenforceable but has the power to reduce the scope or duration of such provision, as the case may be, such provision, in its reduced form, shall then be enforceable.

<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAK" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS; COLOR: #000000">
<HR STYLE="BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 0PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 0PX; WIDTH: 100%; BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 0PX; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN: 4PX 0PX; BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 0PX; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="NOSHADE">
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage115"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 108PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 5.14PT">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	Notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, to the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, the settlement of the Market Stock Units (including any dividend equivalent rights) to be made to the Grantee pursuant to this Agreement is intended to qualify as a "short-term deferral" pursuant to Section 1.409A-1(b)(4) of the U.S. Treasury Regulations and this Agreement shall be interpreted consistently therewith.&#160; However, under certain circumstances, settlement of the Market Stock Units or any dividend equivalent rights may not so qualify, and in that case, the Committee shall administer the grant and settlement of such Market Stock Units and any dividend equivalent rights in strict compliance with Section 409A of the Code.&#160; Further, notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, if at the time of a Participant's termination of employment with the Company, the Participant is a "specified employee" as defined in Section 409A of the Code, and the deferral of the commencement of any payments or benefits otherwise payable hereunder as a result of such termination of service is necessary in order to prevent the imposition of any accelerated or additional tax under Section 409A of the Code, then the Company will defer the commencement of the payment of any such payments or benefits hereunder (without any reduction in such payments or benefits ultimately paid or provided to the Participant) to the minimum extent necessary to satisfy Section 409A of the Code until the date that is six months and one day following the Participant's termination of employment with the Company (or the earliest date as is permitted under Section 409A of the Code), if such payment or benefit is payable upon a termination of employment.&#160; Each payment of Market Stock Units (and related dividend equivalent rights) constitutes a "separate payment" for purposes of Section 409A of the Code.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">

<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEHEADER" STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; COLOR: #000000">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	EXHIBIT A
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	Performance Period:&#160;
</FONT>
	The three year period beginning on
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	INSERT DATE
</FONT>
	.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	Performance Goal
</FONT>
	:
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	Subject to the remaining provisions of this paragraph, the number of Market Stock Units earned shall be determined based on the compounded annual total shareholder return of the Company's Stock over the Performance Period. Compounded annual total shareholder return will be calculated using a beginning price equal to
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	BEGINNING PRICE
</FONT>
	, and an ending price equal to the trading volume weighted average price of the Company's Stock over the period beginning ten (10) calendar days prior to the End Date of the Performance Period and ending on the End Date of the Performance Period, and accounting for immediate reinvestment (as of the ex-dividend date) of all cash dividends and other cash distributions (excluding cash distributions resulting from share repurchases or redemptions by the Company) over this period. In the event Grantee's employment terminates under the circumstances described in
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 3.2
</U>
</FONT>
	or the Market Stock Units are settled pursuant to
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 5.2
</U>
</FONT>
	, the ending price shall be equal to the trading volume weighted average price of the Company's Stock over the period beginning ten (10) calendar days prior to the termination of Grantee's employment (or Change in Control, if applicable), and the compounded annual total shareholder return shall be determined as if such ending price were the price on the End Date of the Performance Period (which, for the avoidance doubt, would remain the third anniversary of the Grant Date).
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; COLOR: #000000; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	The Target Award set forth in
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Section 1
</U>
</FONT>
	of this Agreement shall be multiplied by the applicable percentage set forth in the table below (rounded to the nearest full share), with earned amounts above the 15% and below the 30% thresholds and above the 30% and below the 45% thresholds listed below determined by the Committee using straight-line interpolation:
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<BR>
</DIV>

<A NAME="eolPage118"></A>
<A NAME="EX10-71_HTM"></A>
<EFX_EXHIBIT_10>
<A NAME="FIS_EXHIBIT_10_4"></A>
<DIV>
<HR STYLE="BORDER-TOP: BLACK 4PX SOLID; HEIGHT: 10PX; BORDER-BOTTOM: BLACK 1PX SOLID; COLOR: #FFFFFF; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; MARGIN-LEFT: AUTO; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF; MARGIN-RIGHT: AUTO">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	Exhibit 10.71
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	HEALTHWAYS, INC.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	MARKET STOCK UNIT AWARD AGREEMENT
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	This MARKET STOCK UNIT AWARD AGREEMENT (the "
<U>
	Agreement
</U>
	"), dated
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	GRANT DATE
</FONT>
	(the "
<U>
	Grant Date
</U>
	") is by and between Healthways, Inc., a Delaware corporation (the "
<U>
	Company
</U>
	"), and
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	PARTICIPANT NAME
</FONT>
	(the "
<U>
	Grantee
</U>
	").&#160; Terms not otherwise defined herein shall have the meanings given to them in the Grantee's employment agreement with the Company (as may be amended from time to time, the "
<U>
	Employment Agreement
</U>
	").
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 1.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Market Stock Unit Award; Performance Goals
</U>
	.&#160; Subject to adjustment as set forth herein, the Grantee is hereby granted
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	NUMBER OF UNITS
</FONT>
	restricted stock units (the "
<U>
	Target Award
</U>
	"), with the specific number of restricted stock units earned to be determined in accordance with
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
	hereto (the "
<U>
	Market Stock Units
</U>
	").&#160; Each Market Stock Unit represents the right to receive one share of the Company's Common Stock, $.001 par value (the "
<U>
	Stock
</U>
	"), subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement.&#160; Except as otherwise provided in
<U>
	Section 3
</U>
	or
<U>
	Section 5.2
</U>
	, before the Market Stock Units will be earned and settled, the Compensation Committee (the "
<U>
	Committee
</U>
	") of the Company's board of directors (the "
<U>
	Board
</U>
	") must certify the level of achievement of the Performance Goals described in
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
	hereto which the Committee shall do as soon as practicable after the third anniversary of the Grant Date (the "
<U>
	End Date of the Performance Period
</U>
	", and such period, the "
<U>
	Performance Period
</U>
	").&#160; Any Market Stock Units that are not earned as a result of the level of achievement of the Performance Goals at the End Date of the Performance Period shall be immediately forfeited as of the End Date of the Performance Period.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 2.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Vesting of the Award
</U>
	.&#160; Except as otherwise provided in
<U>
	Section 3
</U>
	and
<U>
	Section 5.2
</U>
	below, 100% of the Market Stock Units determined by the Committee to be earned pursuant to
<U>
	Section 1
</U>
	hereof will vest on the End Date of the Performance Period (the "
<U>
	Vesting Date
</U>
	"), as long as the Grantee is serving as an employee of the Company on such date.&#160; The Company shall issue one share of the Stock to the Grantee in settlement of each earned and vested Market Stock Unit (in the aggregate, the "
<U>
	Distributed Shares
</U>
	") at the time the Market Stock Unit vests pursuant to this Agreement.&#160; The Distributed Shares shall be represented by a certificate or by a book-entry.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 3.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Forfeiture on Termination of Employment
</U>
	.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 40.5PT">
	3.1.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Termination by the Company for Cause
</U>
	.&#160; If the Grantee's employment with the Company is involuntarily terminated for Cause prior to the End Date of the Performance Period, then all Market Stock Units will be forfeited and the Grantee shall have no further rights with respect to such Market Stock Units.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	3.2.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Termination by the Company without Cause or by the Grantee for Good Reason
</U>
	. If Grantee's employment with the Company (a) is involuntarily terminated by the Company for any reason other than termination for Cause, or (b) is terminated by the Grantee for Good Reason, then, subject to Grantee's execution of any release of claims provided for in the Employment Agreement, if applicable, the Vesting Date shall be the effective date of Grantee's termination of employment, and the number of Market Stock Units that shall vest (the "
<U>
	Pro Rata Amount
</U>
	") shall be the product of (i) a fraction, the numerator of which is the number of whole months during the Performance Period that the Grantee was employed by the Company, and the denominator of which is the number of months in the originally stated Performance Period, multiplied by (ii) the number of Market Stock Units that would vest pursuant to
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
	if the Performance Goals that had been achieved as of the Vesting Date were in fact achieved on the End Date of the Performance Period, as further described on
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
	. The Pro Rata Amount of Market Stock Units shall be settled in Stock issued to the Grantee as soon as practicable following the Vesting Date. For purposes of this
<U>
	Section 3.2
</U>
	, the terms "
<U>
	Cause
</U>
	" and "
<U>
	Good Reason
</U>
	" shall have the meanings set forth in the Employment Agreement, or in the absence of an Employment Agreement, the term "
<U>
	Cause
</U>
	" shall mean
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
	(i) a felony conviction of Grantee or the failure of Grantee to contest prosecution for a felony, or (ii) Grantee's willful misconduct or dishonesty, which is directly and materially harmful to the business or reputation of the Company or any of its affiliates
</FONT>
	, and the term "
<U>
	Good Reason
</U>
	" shall mean (i) a material reduction in the Grantee's base salary (unless such reduction is part of an across the board reduction affecting all Company executives with a comparable title), or (ii) a requirement by the Company to relocate the Grantee to a location that is greater than 25 miles from the location of the office in which the Grantee performs his or her duties at the time of such relocation.
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAKAREA" STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 10PT; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN-TOP: 10PT">
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGENUMBERAREA" STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAK" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS">

</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage119"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	3.3.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Termination by Death or Disability
</U>
	.&#160; If the Grantee's employment with the Company terminates by reason of death or Disability (as defined below), then the Vesting Date shall be the date of Grantee's death or the effective date of Grantee's termination of employment on account of Disability, and the number of Market Stock Units that shall vest shall be the product of (i) a fraction, the numerator of which is the number of whole months during the Performance Period that the Grantee was employed by the Company, and the denominator of which is the number of months in the originally stated Performance Period, multiplied by (ii) the Target Award. The Market Stock Units shall be settled in Stock issued to the Grantee (or Grantee's estate or personal representative, as applicable) as soon as practicable following the Vesting Date.&#160;
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
	For purposes of this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<U>
	Section 3.3
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
	, the term "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<U>
	Disability
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
	" shall have the meaning set forth in the Employment Agreement, or in the absence of an Employment Agreement, the term "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
<U>
	Disability
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
	" shall mean the following: (i) Grantee is unable to engage in any substantial gainful activity by reason of any medically determinable physical or mental impairment that can be expected to result in death or can be expected to last for a continuous period of not less than 12 months, or (ii) Grantee is, by reason of any medically determinable physical or mental impairment that can be expected to result in death or can be expected to last for a continuous period of not less than 12 months, receiving income replacement benefits for a period of not less than three months under an accident and health plan covering employees of the Company.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR: #000000">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;3.4&#160; &#160; &#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Termination by Reason of Retirement
</U>
	.&#160; If the Grantee's employment with the Company terminates by reason of Retirement, the Market Stock Units granted hereunder shall not be forfeited but shall be settled in Stock to the Grantee in the manner as described in
<U>
	Section 2
</U>
	(or otherwise) as if the Grantee had continued employment through the Vesting Date (or such other vesting event pursuant to
<U>
	Section 3.3
</U>
	or
<U>
	Section 5.2
</U>
	).&#160; For the purposes of this Agreement, "
<U>
	Retirement
</U>
	" shall mean Normal or Early Retirement. "
<U>
	Early Retirement
</U>
	" shall be deemed to have occurred if: (i) the sum of Grantee's age plus years of employment at the Company as of the proposed early retirement date is equal to or greater than 70, (ii) Grantee has given&#160;written notice to the Company at least one year prior to the proposed early retirement date of his or her intent to retire and&#160;(iii) the Chief Executive Officer of the Company shall have approved in writing such early retirement request prior to the proposed early retirement date, provided that in the event the Chief Executive Officer of the Company does not approve the request for early retirement or the Chief Executive Officer of the Company is Grantee giving notice of his or her intent to retire, then in both cases, the Committee shall make the determination of whether to approve or disapprove such request. "
<U>
	Normal Retirement
</U>
	" means retirement from active employment with the Company or any subsidiary or affiliate of the Company on or after age 65.
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAKAREA" STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 10PT; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN-TOP: 10PT">
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGENUMBERAREA" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	2
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAK" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS">
<HR STYLE="BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 0PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 0PX; WIDTH: 100%; BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 0PX; COLOR: #000000; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN: 4PX 0PX; BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 0PX; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="NOSHADE">
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage120"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
	3.5.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<U>
	Other Termination
</U>
	.&#160; Subject to
<U>
	Section 5.2
</U>
	, if the Grantee's employment with the Company is terminated for any reason other than as described in
<U>
	Sections 3.1
</U>
	through
<U>
	3.4
</U>
	above (or if Grantee fails to execute any release of claims pursuant to the Employment Agreement, if applicable), then all Market Stock Units that have not vested prior to the date of termination of Grantee's employment will be forfeited and the Grantee shall have no further rights with respect to such Market Stock Units.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF">
<BR>
</FONT>
</FONT>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 4.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Voting Rights and Dividends
</U>
	.&#160; Prior to the Vesting Date, the Grantee shall be credited with cash dividend equivalents with respect to the Market Stock Units
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	&#160;
</FONT>
	at the time of any payment of dividends to stockholders on shares of Common Stock, and such dividend equivalents shall be paid (in cash, without interest) to the Grantee when the Market Stock Units to which they relate are settled in accordance with this Agreement.&#160; The Grantee shall not have any voting rights with respect to the Stock underlying the Market Stock Units prior to the vesting of the Market Stock Units and the issuance of the Stock as set forth in
<U>
	Section 2
</U>
	.&#160; A holder of Distributed Shares shall have full dividend and voting rights as a holder of Stock.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 5.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Restrictions on Transfer; Change in Control
</U>
	.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
	5.1.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	General Restrictions
</U>
	.&#160; The Market Stock Units shall not be transferable by the Grantee (or his or her personal representative or estate) other than by will or by the laws of descent and distribution.&#160; The terms of this Agreement shall be binding on the executors, administrators, heirs and successors of the Grantee.
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAKAREA" STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 10PT; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN-TOP: 10PT">
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGENUMBERAREA" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	3
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAK" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS">
<HR STYLE="BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 0PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 0PX; WIDTH: 100%; BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 0PX; COLOR: #000000; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN: 4PX 0PX; BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 0PX; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="NOSHADE">
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage121"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
	5.2.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Change in Control
</U>
	.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 85.5PT">
	(a)
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If in connection with a Change in Control, the acquiring corporation (or other successor to the Company in the Change in Control) does not assume the Market Stock Units, then a number of Market Stock Units shall vest and be settled in Stock issued to the Grantee immediately prior to the Change in Control equal to the greater of (A) the Target Award, or (B) the number of Market Stock Units that would vest pursuant to
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
	if the Performance Goals that had been achieved as of the date of the Change in Control had in fact been achieved as of the End Date of the Performance Period. For purposes of this Agreement, a "
<U>
	Change in Control
</U>
	" shall mean the following: (i) any person or entity, including a "group" as defined in Section 13(d)(3) of the Exchange Act, other than the Company or a wholly-owned subsidiary thereof or any employee benefit plan of the Company or any of its subsidiaries, becomes the beneficial owner of the Company's securities having 35% or more of the combined voting power of the then outstanding securities of the Company that may be cast for the election of directors of the Company (other than as a result of an issuance of securities initiated by the Company in the ordinary course of business); or (ii) as the result of, or in connection with, any cash tender or exchange offer, merger or other business combination, sales of assets or contested election, or any combination of the foregoing transactions, less than a majority of the combined voting power of the then outstanding securities of the Company or any successor corporation or entity entitled to vote generally in the election of the directors of the Company or such other corporation or entity after such transaction are held in the aggregate by the holders of the Company's securities entitled to vote generally in the election of directors of the Company immediately prior to such transaction, in substantially the same proportions as their ownership, immediately prior to such transaction or transactions; or (iii) during any period of two consecutive years, individuals who at the beginning of any such period constitute the Board cease for any reason to constitute at least a majority thereof, unless the election, or the nomination for election by the Company's stockholders, of each director of the Company first elected during such period was approved by a vote of at least two-thirds of the directors of the Company then still in office who were directors of the Company at the beginning of any such period.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 90PT">
	(b)
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If in connection with a Change in Control, the acquiring corporation&#160; (or other successor to the Company in the Change in Control) assumes the Market Stock Units, and if Grantee's employment with the Company (or its successor company) (i) is involuntarily terminated within 12 months following a Change in Control for any reason other than termination for Cause, or (ii) is terminated by the Grantee for Good Reason within 12 months following a Change in Control, then subject to Grantee's execution of any release of claims set forth in the Employment Agreement, if applicable, the Vesting Date shall be the date of the termination of employment described in this
<U>
	Section 5.2(b)
</U>
	, and a number of Market Stock Units shall vest and be settled in Stock issued to the Grantee on the Vesting Date equal to the greater of (A) the Target Award, or (B) the number of Market Stock Units that would vest pursuant to
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
	if the Performance Goals that had been achieved as of the Vesting Date were in fact achieved as of the End Date of the Performance Period. For purposes of this
<U>
	Section 5.2(b
</U>
	), the terms "
<U>
	Cause
</U>
	" and "
<U>
	Good Reason
</U>
	" shall have the meanings set forth in
<U>
	Section 3.2
</U>
	.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 6.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Restrictive Agreement
</U>
	.&#160; As a condition to the receipt of any Distributed Shares, the Grantee (or his or her legal representative or estate or any third party transferee), if the Company so requests, will execute an agreement in form satisfactory to the Company in which the Grantee or such other recipient of the shares represents that he or she is purchasing the shares for investment purposes, and not with a view to resale or distribution.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 7.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Market Stock Units Award Subject to Recoupment Policy
</U>
	. The award of Market Stock Units is subject to the Healthways, Inc. Compensation Recoupment Policy (the "
<U>
	Policy
</U>
	").&#160; The award of Market Stock Units, or any amount traceable to the award of Market Stock Units, shall be subject to the recoupment obligations described in the Policy.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 8.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Adjustment
</U>
	.&#160; In the event of any merger, reorganization, consolidation, recapitalization, extraordinary cash dividend, stock dividend, stock split or other change in corporate structure affecting the Stock, the number of Market Stock Units subject to this Agreement, as well as the performance criteria set forth on
<U>
	Exhibit A
</U>
	, shall be equitably and proportionately adjusted by the Committee in accordance with the intent of this Agreement without duplication of
<U>
	Section 4
</U>
	.
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAKAREA" STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 10PT; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN-TOP: 10PT">
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGENUMBERAREA" STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	4
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEBREAK" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS">
<HR STYLE="BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 0PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 0PX; WIDTH: 100%; BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 0PX; COLOR: #000000; CLEAR: BOTH; MARGIN: 4PX 0PX; BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 0PX; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="NOSHADE">
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage122"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 9.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Tax Withholding
</U>
	.&#160; The Company shall have the right to require the Grantee to remit to the Company an amount necessary to satisfy any federal, state and local withholding tax requirements attributable to the vesting and payment of the Market Stock Units prior to the delivery of the Distributed Shares, or may withhold from the Distributed Shares an amount of Stock having a Fair Market Value equal to such federal, state or local taxes as shall be required to be withheld pursuant to any applicable law or regulation.&#160; For the purposes of this Agreement, "
<U>
	Fair Market Value
</U>
	" shall mean with respect to the Stock, as of any given date or dates, unless otherwise determined by the Committee in good faith, the reported closing price of a share of such class of Stock on the Nasdaq Stock Market ("
<U>
	Nasdaq
</U>
	") or such other exchange or market as is the principal trading market for such class of Stock, or, if no such sale of a share of such class of Stock is reported on the Nasdaq or other exchange or principal trading market on such date, the fair market value of a share of such class of Stock as determined by the Committee in good faith.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 10.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	[Intentionally Omitted.]
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 11.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Confidentiality, Non-Solicitation and Non-Compete.
</U>
	In the event Grantee breaches any of the confidentiality, non-solicitation or non-compete covenants set forth in the Employment Agreement, if applicable, the Market Stock Units shall immediately thereupon expire and be forfeited, and the Company shall be entitled to seek other appropriate remedies it may have available in connection with such breach.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 36PT">
	Section 12.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Miscellaneous
</U>
	.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
	12.1.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Entire Agreement
</U>
	.&#160; This Agreement and the Employment Agreement contain the entire understanding and agreement between the Company and the Grantee concerning the Market Stock Units granted hereby, and supersede any prior or contemporaneous negotiations and understandings.&#160; The Company and the Grantee have made no promises, agreements, conditions, or understandings relating to the Market Stock Units, either orally or in writing, that are not included in this Agreement or the Employment Agreement.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
	12.2.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Employment
</U>
	.&#160; By entering into this Agreement, the Company does not give the Grantee any right to continue to be employed by the Company or to be entitled to any remuneration or benefits not set forth in this Agreement or the Employment Agreement.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
	12.3.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Captions
</U>
	.&#160; The captions and section numbers appearing in this Agreement are inserted only as a matter of convenience.&#160; They do not define, limit, construe, or describe the scope or intent of the provisions of this Agreement.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
	12.4.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Counterparts
</U>
	.&#160; This Agreement may be executed in counterparts, each of which when signed by the Company and the Grantee will be deemed an original and all of which together will be deemed the same Agreement.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL">
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: ARIAL; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 72PT">
	12.5.
<FONT ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Notice
</U>
	.&#160; All notices required to be given under this Agreement shall be deemed to be received if delivered or mailed as provided for herein, to the parties at the following addresses, or to such other address as either party may provide in writing from time to time.
<BR>
</DIV>

<U>
	Governing Law
</U>
